# ─── Personal / sensitive data ────────────────────────────────────────
# Local resume/LinkedIn drafts — not for the public repo.
docs/resume-bullets.md
docs/cursor-models.md
push-to-github.ps1
# The data/ folder under each backend instance holds PII:
#   - match_registry.json  : every job you've matched (your search history)
#   - decision_log.json    : every job you starred / passed
#   - tracker.json         : your application tracker
#   - user.json            : your name, email, etc.
#   - resume/, resumes/    : actual resume files (PDF/DOCX)
#   - parsed/              : structured profile (name, experience, skills)
#   - cover_letters/       : generated drafts that mention you by name
#   - feedback_embeddings.json : derived from your starred/passed history
# None of this should ever leave your machine.
lantern/api/data/
archive/sentinel/data/
archive/data/

# Backend logs — contain timestamps + request paths from your local use
lantern/api/logs/
archive/sentinel/logs/
archive/logs/
*.log
*.log.*
*.err

# Runtime config — start.ps1 / start.sh copy lantern/api/config.example.json
# to lantern/api/config.json on first run. Edit config.json (not the example)
# for personal tuning so pulling repo updates won't overwrite your local
# settings. Treat config.json as containing potential secrets (Discord
# webhook, SMTP password) and never commit it.
lantern/api/config.json
archive/sentinel/config.json
!lantern/api/config.example.json

